    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/2403.13372v4</id>
    <title>LlamaFactory: Unified Efficient Fine-Tuning of 100+ Language Models</title>
    <updated>2024-06-27T22:44:48Z</updated>
    <link href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2403.13372v4" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/>
    <link href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/2403.13372v4" rel="related" type="application/pdf" title="pdf"/>
    <summary>Efficient fine-tuning is vital for adapting large language models (LLMs) to downstream tasks. However, it requires non-trivial efforts to implement these methods on different models. We present LlamaFactory, a unified framework that integrates a suite of cutting-edge efficient training methods. It provides a solution for flexibly customizing the fine-tuning of 100+ LLMs without the need for coding through the built-in web UI LlamaBoard. We empirically validate the efficiency and effectiveness of our framework on language modeling and text generation tasks. It has been released at https://github.com/hiyouga/LLaMA-Factory and received over 25,000 stars and 3,000 forks.</summary>
